00:16:54.160 --> 00:16:56.140
to the stage, but I'm going
to tell you a little bit

00:16:56.140 --> 00:16:58.350
about him just in
case you didn't know.

00:16:58.350 --> 00:17:01.580
For the past two
years Gene has served

00:17:01.580 --> 00:17:05.550
as the 5th national Ambassador
for Young People's Literature.

00:17:05.550 --> 00:17:08.320
He was born and raised in
California and is the son

00:17:08.320 --> 00:17:09.880
of Chinese immigrants,

00:17:09.880 --> 00:17:12.350
he has been drawing
comics since the 5th grade.

00:17:12.350 --> 00:17:18.330
In 2006, his book, American
Born Chinese was published

00:17:18.330 --> 00:17:21.260
and it became the first
graphic novel to be nominated

00:17:21.260 --> 00:17:24.790
for a National Book Award
and it was the first

00:17:24.790 --> 00:17:28.070
to win the American Library
Association's Prints Award.

00:17:28.070 --> 00:17:32.430
In 2013, his two
volume graphic novel

00:17:32.430 --> 00:17:34.310
about the Boxer Rebellion
entitled:

00:17:34.310 --> 00:17:36.930
Boxers and Saints was
not nominated as well

00:17:36.930 --> 00:17:41.800
for a National Book Award and
won the L.A. Times Book Prize.

00:17:41.800 --> 00:17:45.360
In addition and I could go on
but, in addition to cartooning,

00:17:45.360 --> 00:17:47.560
he is also a teacher,

00:17:47.560 --> 00:17:49.810
he is currently teaching
creative writing

00:17:49.810 --> 00:17:53.930
and he has been a tremendous
National Ambassador.

00:17:53.930 --> 00:17:58.410
His platform, Reading Without
Walls has challenged all of us

00:17:58.410 --> 00:18:01.510
to stretch our reading habits
in very important ways, Gene?

00:18:01.510 --> 00:18:11.040
[Applauding]

00:18:11.040 --> 00:18:12.900
&gt;&gt; Good morning everyone.

00:18:12.900 --> 00:18:14.200
&gt;&gt; [All together] Good morning.

00:18:14.200 --> 00:18:16.550
&gt;&gt; I am so excited to be here.

00:18:16.550 --> 00:18:19.130
Two years ago in this same
building in a different room,

00:18:19.130 --> 00:18:23.700
but the same building I got
the fanciest thing that I own,

00:18:23.700 --> 00:18:28.030
got the National Ambassador for
Young People Literature medal

00:18:28.030 --> 00:18:30.730
from the Library of Congress,
from ever Every Child a reader,

00:18:30.730 --> 00:18:32.560
from the Children's
Books Council

00:18:32.560 --> 00:18:36.290
and the last two years have
been among the most amazing

00:18:36.290 --> 00:18:37.590
of my life.

00:18:37.590 --> 00:18:40.690
I want to thank Dr. Hayden and
Carl and Shawn and everyone else

00:18:40.690 --> 00:18:41.990
for all of your support.

00:18:41.990 --> 00:18:46.330
I want to especially thank the
librarians and the teachers

00:18:46.330 --> 00:18:49.600
and the booksellers that have
made these past two years

00:18:49.600 --> 00:18:50.900
so magical.

00:18:50.900 --> 00:18:53.020
For the last two years I've
gotten to go around the country

00:18:53.020 --> 00:18:57.680
to talk to young people from all
different communities in America

00:18:57.680 --> 00:19:01.990
and what I've discovered
is that kids love books,

00:19:01.990 --> 00:19:05.930
despite what some adults
might lead you to think,

00:19:05.930 --> 00:19:09.890
kids still love books,
and they love books

00:19:09.890 --> 00:19:11.690
for the same reason
we all love books it's

00:19:11.690 --> 00:19:16.540
because stories help us
make sense of our lives,

00:19:16.540 --> 00:19:22.520
stories help us make sense of
the world and that's why I am

00:19:22.520 --> 00:19:25.380
so excited to be here
today because today,

00:19:25.380 --> 00:19:28.040
we all in this room,
we get to witness one

00:19:28.040 --> 00:19:31.460
of the greatest storytellers
of our time,

00:19:31.460 --> 00:19:36.490
receive the National Ambassador
for Young People's medal,

00:19:36.490 --> 00:19:43.150
Jacqueline Woodson is one of
my heroes, she is a person

00:19:43.150 --> 00:19:45.860
that I deeply admire, I admire
her, not just as a writer,

00:19:45.860 --> 00:19:48.370
but also a human being.

00:19:48.370 --> 00:19:51.960
In many ways I believe that her
ambassadorship is simply going

00:19:51.960 --> 00:19:55.850
to be an extension of the
work she's already doing.

00:19:55.850 --> 00:19:59.080
If you've have had the
pleasure of reading one

00:19:59.080 --> 00:20:02.250
of Jackie's books, if you
had the pleasure of sitting

00:20:02.250 --> 00:20:03.830
in on one of her speeches,

00:20:03.830 --> 00:20:07.440
you know that through her
words whether they're spoken

00:20:07.440 --> 00:20:12.290
into a microphone or written
on a page, she teaches us

00:20:12.290 --> 00:20:15.470
about the world, she helps
us make since of life

00:20:15.470 --> 00:20:19.590
and make sense of the world,
her words bring us hope,

00:20:19.590 --> 00:20:22.570
her words bring about change.

00:20:22.570 --> 00:20:25.500
Like I said, she's one of my
heroes and if she isn't one

00:20:25.500 --> 00:20:29.130
of yours yet, give her a few
minutes, wait until she gets

00:20:29.130 --> 00:20:31.710
up here, she'll be
one of yours too.

00:20:31.710 --> 00:20:36.400
Thank you all for being here, I
know you all are just as excited

00:20:36.400 --> 00:20:40.430
as me to celebrate
Ambassador Jacqueline Woodson.

00:20:40.430 --> 00:20:42.230
Thank you so much.

00:20:42.230 --> 00:20:51.430
[Applauding]

00:20:51.430 --> 00:20:55.510
&gt;&gt; Thank you Gene and thank you
for your last two years, really.

00:20:55.510 --> 00:21:05.180
[Applauding]

00:21:05.180 --> 00:21:07.370
I ask Gene to stay here
with me and now I'm going

00:21:07.370 --> 00:21:12.530
to ask Dr. Hayden to join
us because we're going

00:21:12.530 --> 00:21:17.200
to start telling you
really cool things

00:21:17.200 --> 00:21:20.670
about Jackie [laughter]
Jacqueline Woodson is the author

00:21:20.670 --> 00:21:25.320
of more than two dozen award
winning books for young adults,

00:21:25.320 --> 00:21:28.030
middle graders, and children.

00:21:28.030 --> 00:21:33.570
Her books address important
topics such as: Bullying

00:21:33.570 --> 00:21:38.770
and kindness, incarceration,
identity,

00:21:38.770 --> 00:21:43.240
mixed race experiences,
and much more.

00:21:43.240 --> 00:21:48.600
Among her many accolades, she
is a four time Newbery Winner,

00:21:48.600 --> 00:21:52.040
a three time National
Book Award Finalist

00:21:52.040 --> 00:21:55.670
and a two time Coretta
Scott King Award winner.

00:21:55.670 --> 00:22:03.640
For some specifics, Gene or Dr.
Hayden, either way [laughter]

00:22:03.640 --> 00:22:07.310
&gt;&gt; In 2014, she received
the National Book Award

00:22:07.310 --> 00:22:10.040
for your New York Times
bestselling memoir,

00:22:10.040 --> 00:22:11.910
"Brown Girl Dreaming"
you all read this book?

00:22:11.910 --> 00:22:13.930
You haven't read this book, you
should be a little bit ashamed,

00:22:13.930 --> 00:22:16.730
it's an amazing book
[applauding]

00:22:19.660 --> 00:22:23.330
which was also a recipient of
the Coretta Scott King Award,

00:22:23.330 --> 00:22:30.800
a Newbery Honor, the NAACP Image
Award and the Sibert Honor.

00:22:30.800 --> 00:22:36.280
In 2015, Jacqueline Woodson was
named the Young People's Poet

00:22:36.280 --> 00:22:39.120
Laureate by the Poetry
Foundation and some

00:22:39.120 --> 00:22:44.830
of her other books include:
"The Other Side" "Each Kindness"

00:22:44.830 --> 00:22:50.090
"Coming on Home Soon" "Feathers"
"Show a Way" "After Tupac"

00:22:50.090 --> 00:22:52.970
and "D Foster" and
"Miracle's Boys"

00:23:02.200 --> 00:23:03.880
&gt;&gt; She is also the recipient

00:23:03.880 --> 00:23:07.480
of the Margaret Alexander
Edwards Award

00:23:07.480 --> 00:23:10.750
for lifetime achievement
for her contributions

00:23:10.750 --> 00:23:12.370
to young adult Literature,

00:23:12.370 --> 00:23:15.750
the winner of the Jane
Addams Children's Book Award

00:23:15.750 --> 00:23:19.780
and was the 2013
United States nominee

00:23:19.780 --> 00:23:24.730
for the Hans Christian
Andersen Award and this March,

00:23:24.730 --> 00:23:28.820
Penguin Young Readers will
celebrate the 20th anniversary

00:23:28.820 --> 00:23:33.830
of her, "If You Come Softly"
with a special addition

00:23:33.830 --> 00:23:37.200
of the adored story
of star crossed love

00:23:37.200 --> 00:23:40.790
between a black teenage boy
and his Jewish class mate.

00:23:40.790 --> 00:23:49.190
&gt;&gt; And later this year,
The Dream of America,

00:23:49.190 --> 00:23:53.680
a middle grade novel written by
Woodson and The Day You Begin,

00:23:53.680 --> 00:23:56.700
a picture book also written
by Woodson, and illustrated

00:23:56.700 --> 00:24:01.240
by Raphael Lopez, will
be published, but today,

00:24:01.240 --> 00:24:06.470
should we get a drum in here?

00:24:06.470 --> 00:24:11.010
She officially becomes the
6th National Ambassador

00:24:11.010 --> 00:24:14.120
for Young People's
Literature Dr. Hayden is going

00:24:14.120 --> 00:24:18.750
to make it official as
soon as Jackie gets up here

00:24:18.750 --> 00:24:21.510
and places the medallion
around her neck.

00:24:21.510 --> 00:24:31.240
[Applauding]

