So is it still morning?

00:40:20.990 --> 00:40:23.720
Because I start it with
saying good morning.

00:40:23.720 --> 00:40:27.790
Okay. Oh, I have the
lavalier so people

00:40:27.790 --> 00:40:30.350
who are live streaming is
it okay, is my sound okay?

00:40:30.350 --> 00:40:31.930
I'm good, I could
keep using this?

00:40:31.930 --> 00:40:33.230
I could use both of them?

00:40:33.230 --> 00:40:34.930
Thank you.

00:40:34.930 --> 00:40:39.460
So it's an amazing honor to
stand before you in the Library

00:40:39.460 --> 00:40:43.760
of Congress this morning, it's
also an honor to be living

00:40:43.760 --> 00:40:47.160
in this time to bare witness
to our countries beautiful

00:40:47.160 --> 00:40:51.230
and complicated history
and its immense possibility

00:40:51.230 --> 00:40:53.980
because I do believe we're
living in a time of great,

00:40:53.980 --> 00:40:56.190
great, great possibility.

00:40:56.190 --> 00:41:00.890
What an honor to
follow the footsteps

00:41:00.890 --> 00:41:04.930
of groundbreaking ambassador's
that came before me, Gene Yang,

00:41:04.930 --> 00:41:07.460
who is not only my
absolute hero,

00:41:07.460 --> 00:41:09.380
so which makes me
think he read my speech

00:41:09.380 --> 00:41:16.580
because he called me his hero
[laughter] but he's also a hero

00:41:16.580 --> 00:41:19.720
to both my children
and to many children.

00:41:19.720 --> 00:41:22.970
Kate DiCamillo, who is
the inspiration for us,

00:41:22.970 --> 00:41:27.670
naming our cat Fred after Bink
and Gollie, who never fails

00:41:27.670 --> 00:41:29.390
to make me laugh
or make me choke

00:41:29.390 --> 00:41:30.800
up with each book she writes.

00:41:30.800 --> 00:41:34.560
Katherine Paterson one of is one
of the kindest people I know.

00:41:34.560 --> 00:41:37.650
Walter Dean Myers, who came
into the world and left it

00:41:37.650 --> 00:41:41.030
with his untimely passing
filled with a body of work

00:41:41.030 --> 00:41:46.730
that changed consciousness of so
many young men and boys of color

00:41:46.730 --> 00:41:51.830
and so many others as well,.

00:41:51.830 --> 00:41:55.380
I miss Walter.

00:41:56.430 --> 00:42:00.350
Walter, who during his time
as National Ambassador,

00:42:00.350 --> 00:42:04.440
tirelessly traveled and spoke
to the many who had not thought

00:42:04.440 --> 00:42:06.660
of themselves as part
of a bigger world

00:42:06.660 --> 00:42:10.790
or deeper narrative; and of
course, our beloved pioneer,

00:42:10.790 --> 00:42:14.990
Jon Scieszka neighbor,
friend, and awesome writer

00:42:14.990 --> 00:42:18.510
who is sitting among us this
morning I would not be here

00:42:18.510 --> 00:42:20.570
without y' all.

00:42:20.570 --> 00:42:22.810
First and foremost, I
want to thank the people

00:42:22.810 --> 00:42:24.800
who have worked beyond
hard to bring me

00:42:24.800 --> 00:42:28.510
to this moment the not
fabulous Library of Congress

00:42:28.510 --> 00:42:31.380
and Dr. Carla Hayden, my sister

00:42:31.380 --> 00:42:35.470
from another mother
and history maker.

00:42:35.470 --> 00:42:40.020
My dear friend, Debbie
Taylor and all of my people

00:42:40.020 --> 00:42:45.460
at Enoch Pratt Library it
was here doing a reading

00:42:45.460 --> 00:42:48.690
for my first novel,
"Last Summer with Maizon"

00:42:48.690 --> 00:42:53.750
that I rediscovered the
breath and depth of libraries.

00:42:53.750 --> 00:42:56.980
Readings, conversation,
children's programs,

00:42:56.980 --> 00:43:00.700
programs for young mothers,
adult literacy classes,

00:43:00.700 --> 00:43:05.050
passport renewals, puppet
making, all of it was,

00:43:05.050 --> 00:43:11.450
is happening at the libraries,
Enoch Pratt and nationwide.

00:43:11.450 --> 00:43:18.270
As I began to travel, I saw in
every single state the enormity,

00:43:18.270 --> 00:43:22.330
both large and small,
had to offer anyone

00:43:22.330 --> 00:43:24.560
who stepped through their doors.

00:43:24.560 --> 00:43:28.500
I rediscovered that libraries
aren't just for some people,

00:43:28.500 --> 00:43:30.040
they're for all people.

00:43:30.040 --> 00:43:34.350
I'd like to thank The
Children's Book Council,

